SUMMARY: How Deep Is Your Love w/ filmmaker | In Light Human Rights Docum
 entary Film Festival
DESCRIPTION:In How Deep Is Your Love\, marine biologists venture into Ear
 th’s last wilderness—the deep sea—to study "alien-like" creatures and anc
 ient ecosystems thriving in darkness. As they race to map undiscovered sp
 ecies\, the film reveals the urgent threat of deep-sea mining\, poised to
  devastate these fragile habitats. Blending awe-inspiring exploration wit
 h a call to action\, it questions humanity’s commitment to preserving an 
 unseen and mysterious world. [101 min\; documentary\; English]\n\nA Q&A w
 ill follow with filmmaker Eileen Mortimer\, Dr. Teresa Kovacs (Germanic S
 tudies\; Theatre\, Drama and Contemporary Dance)\, Dr. R. Andrés Guzmán (
 Spanish and Portuguese\; Cultural Studies Program)\, and Ahmed Tahsin Sha
 ms (Media School).
CATEGORIES:Free
