 Hull\n\nSunday\, April 12\n\n1 -3 pm\n\nCorrine will be demonstrating the
  versatility of the gouache medium\, sharing her techniques\, explaining 
 how gouache differs from acrylics and oils\, and offering insight into he
 r creative process. Watch as she brings a beautiful piece to life with th
 is unique and expressive medium.\n\nAll are welcome\, free\n\n-----------
 -------------------------------------------------------------------------
 -------------\n\nBrown County Art Guild – A not for profit organization l
 ocated in the heart of downtown Nashville\, Indiana. On display throughou
 t its galleries is a prized collection of historic paintings as well as c
 urrent works for sale from regional award-winning member artists. Also of
 fered throughout the year are artist demonstrations\, workshops\, and spe
 cial exhibits.\n\nGallery hours March through December 2026\, Monday – Sa
 turday\, 11 – 5 and Sunday\, 12 – 4 or by appointment.\n\nIf you would li
 ke more information\, call 812.988.6185 or visit our web site https://bro
 wncountyartguild.org/ https://browncountyartguild.org/
