SUMMARY: “Nature Walk”: Music and Science Come Together
DESCRIPTION:Inspired by an early spring outing led by Distinguished IU Bi
 ology Professor Roger Hangarter https://www.rogerhangarter.net/about \, t
 his unique musical performance depicts the seasonal re-awakening of natur
 e in southern Indiana. Dr. Hangarter has led IU Student composers on a hi
 ke where they observe life in ponds and fields and then compose musical p
 ieces based on their experiences during the hike.\n\nDuring the performan
 ce\, Professor Hangarter will share images and insights about the wildlif
 e encountered during the hike.\n\nOn behalf of the Student Composers Asso
 ciation https://blogs.iu.edu/jsomcomposition/student-composer-association
 / at Indiana University\, Jacobs School of Music https://music.indiana.ed
 u/index.html student composer Thejas Mirle https://www.youtube.com/channe
 l/UCNYV1Gj6BS4EDhp17-WFVbA has organized the musical performance based on
  the creative works and will lead an ensemble in playing the compositions
 . Composers are Noah Burns\, Jacob Lisiewski\, Alexey Logunov\, and Emmet
  Lewis.\n\nThis performance immediately precedes the Artists for Climate 
 Awareness “Art As Inquiry” art show reception https://artistsforclimateaw
 areness.org/event/art-as-inquiry-reception/ \, which begins at 3:00 pm.
CATEGORIES:Bloomington,Gallery,Live,Music
