SUMMARY: Reception for “Art as Inquiry:” A Gallery Show
DESCRIPTION:All ages are invited to explore “Art as Inquiry https://artis
 tsforclimateawareness.org/event/climate-co-lab/ \,” a juried climate‑art 
 exhibition shown at the Pillar Arts Alliance Center\, Bloomington\, IN fr
 om Apr 2–29.\n\nNOTE: This reception directly follows "Nature Walk https:
 //artistsforclimateawareness.org/event/nature-walk-4-12-2026/ \," a music
 al performance\, starting at 2 pm. Please come! Refreshments are availabl
 e and prizes for artwork will be awarded.\n\nFeaturing 2‑D and 3‑D artwor
 ks from 25 artists across several states\, “Art as Inquiry” invites visit
 ors to encounter climate research and climate unease\, ecological change\
 , and environmental justice through the lens of artistic imagination.\n\n
 April 12\, 2–3 pm – Nature Walk https://artistsforclimateawareness.org/ev
 ent/nature-walk-4-12-2026/ \, a musical and narrative performance led by 
 IU Jacobs School of Music student Thejas Mirle https://www.youtube.com/ch
 annel/UCNYV1Gj6BS4EDhp17-WFVbA and four composers\, with narration by Dis
 tinguished IU Biology Professor Roger Hangarter https://www.rogerhangarte
 r.net/about .\n\nApril 12\, 3–5 pm (this event) – Reception https://artis
 tsforclimateawareness.org/event/art-as-inquiry-reception/ for the member 
 climate‑art exhibition\; prizes awarded.\n\nRelated event: Beginning Apri
 l 19\, six more artworks from the Climate Co‑lab https://artistsforclimat
 eawareness.org/event/reception-climate-co-lab/ (organized by Brushes for 
 a Better Planet https://lalithashan10.wixsite.com/brushes-for-a-better ) 
 join the exhibition\, displayed alongside the Art as Inquiry works.
CATEGORIES:Bloomington,Exhibition,Gallery,Visual-Arts
