SUMMARY: Plato's Closet presents the 17th Annual Trashion Refashion Show!
DESCRIPTION:The 17th Annual Trashion Refashion Runway Show\, presented by
  Plato’s Closet\, brings eco-conscious couture back to the Buskirk-Chumle
 y Theater on Sunday\, April 12\, 2026\, at 7 p.m. (doors open at 6:30 p.m
 .). This beloved event blends high fashion with sustainability\, showcasi
 ng over 50 original\, upcycled designs modeled by a diverse cast of commu
 nity members.A highlight of Bloomington’s arts scene since 2010\, the sho
 w promotes environmental sustainability and artistic creativity while cha
 llenging conventional notions about beauty and consumerism. Each of the j
 uried show’s designs consists of at least 90% discarded materials\, eithe
 r rescued from the waste stream (Trashion) or transformed from underutili
 zed garments (Refashion). The show is also committed to cultivating diver
 sity among its models with regard to gender\, age\, race\, body type and 
 other categories.\n\nThis fundraising event to support the Center for Sus
 tainable Living features locally made couture sure to inspire the fashion
  creatives lurking inside us all.\n\nTickets are $22 in advance\, $24 day
 -of\, and $10 for children/students—available at the BCT box office or on
 line:buskirkchumley.org/events/2026-trashion-refashion-runway-show-april-
 12-2026/ https://buskirkchumley.org/events/2026-trashion-refashion-runway
 -show-april-12-2026/\n\nProudly sponsored by: Plato’s Closet\, Bikesmiths
 \, Hickory Audiology\, Friends of Gail Kincaid\, Alibi Boutique\, and Oly
 mpus Properties.\n\nFor event details and updates\, visit http://blooming
 tontrashion.org.
CATEGORIES:Bloomington,Live,Visual-Arts,Tickets
