SUMMARY: African American Dance Company Spring Concert
DESCRIPTION:The legendary African American Dance Company presents its Ann
 ual Spring Concert on Saturday\, April 18\, 2026\, 7:30 p.m. at Buskirk-C
 humley Theater in Bloomington\, IN.\n\nDirected by Baba Stafford C. Berry
  Jr.\, the African American Dance Company shares movement traditions from
  Africa\, the diaspora\, and from African American culture. Since its fou
 nding in 1974\, the African American Dance Company has performed througho
 ut Indiana\, in New York City\, and internationally in China\, Jamaica\, 
 and Cuba. The company’s repertoire includes African dance styles\, contem
 porary\, modern\, jazz\, hip-hop\, and various cultural forms.\n\nThe Afr
 ican American Dance Company is a course offered for credit through the De
 partment of African American and African Diaspora Studies\, and is one of
  three performing ensembles managed by African American Arts Institute at
  Indiana University Bloomington.
CATEGORIES:Bloomington,Dance,In-Person,Live
