SUMMARY: When Everyone Swims w/ filmmaker | New Americas Cinema
DESCRIPTION:When Everyone Swims is a compilation of inspirational and ins
 ightful stories about how everyone deserves access to pools and safe plac
 es to swim. Through powerful\, personal narratives\, the film celebrates 
 resilience and highlights how water literacy can help individuals from al
 l backgrounds build healthy\, life-affirming relationships with the water
 . [90 min\; documentary\; English]\n\nA Q&A with director Jerald Harkness
 \, Olympic medalist Lilly King\, and production consultant Dr. Tiffany Mo
 nique Quash\, moderated by Bill Ramos of the School of Public Health\, wi
 ll follow the screening.
