SUMMARY: Moulin Rouge! | Pop Music(als)!
DESCRIPTION:Set against the Parisian backdrop of a spectacular Moulin Rou
 ge show\, an idealistic young writer (Ewan McGregor) is drafted into a bo
 hemian entourage and falls in love with an ambitious\, stunning\, and ult
 imately doomed courtesan (Nicole Kidman)\, who is caught between the hero
  she's falling for\, too\, and a ruthless duke\, whose fortune could help
  save her and the Moulin Rouge. McGregor and Kidman lead an international
 ly renowned cast in this swooningly romantic and pop-music-inspired danci
 ng and singing extravaganza with musical inspiration from the likes of Da
 vid Bowie\, Beck\, Labelle\, Madonna\, and Fatboy Slim. The film would go
  on to inspire the Broadway stage production of Moulin Rouge! The Musical
 . [127 min\; musical\, drama\, romance\; English\, French\, and Spanish w
 ith English subtitles]
